New Features and Important Changes in GammaLib 1.0.0

Author(s) : Juergen Knoedlseder

24 November 2015


1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly summarizes module by module the most important changes
made since the last release of GammaLib.


2. Public interface modifications
---------------------------------
None


3. Configuration
-----------------
The __init__.py file in the pyext/gammalib folder is now only created during
build but not during the install. This should avoid problems during installation
related to file access rights (#1569).

A special post processing of the Python module libraries has been added for
Mac OS X 10.11 and higher (El Capitan). This post processing is a replacement for
setting DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH during unit testing since the environment variable is
ignored in certain circumstances by El Capitan.


