12. Sky module
--------------
Remove the following methods from GSkyRegions as we have not identified a use case
where this access is needed (#1564):
* set(std::string, GSkyRegion)
* insert(std::string, GSkyRegion)
* remove(std::string)
* operator[](std::string)
* contains(std::string)
* get_index(std::string)

The Python extension GSkyMap::__getitem__ now checks the validity of the index and
map number and throws an out_of_range exception if the parameters are not valid.
This is required on some platforms to properly catch the end in iterations (#1581).


13. Support module
------------------
The gammalib::expand_env() function now handles ~, ~user, ~+ and ~- following the
logic implemented for the bash shell.


